S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
A N A C T
RELATING TO PROPERTY -- BY POSSESSION AND PRESCRIPTION
Introduced By: Senators LaMountain, and Vargas
Date Introduced: February 26, 2025
Referred To: Senate Judiciary
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 34-7-4 of the General Laws in Chapter 34-7 entitled "By Possession
2 and Prescription" is hereby amended to read as follows:
3 34-7-4. Right of footway denied.
4 No right of footway, except within one hundred (100) yards of the Pawtuxet River in the
5 cities of Warwick and Cranston or claimed in connection with a right to pass with carriages, shall
6 be acquired by prescription or adverse use for any length of time.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
